# widget — data layer boundary

The widget talks to the backend through ONE narrow seam. Keep it that way as
the real UI lands in W3/W4.

## Invariants

- **All API access goes through `src/api/chatClient.ts`.** No raw `fetch`,
  `axios`, or `XMLHttpRequest` in components, hooks, or anywhere else.
- **Components read and write chat state via the Zustand store**
  (`src/store/chatStore.ts`) — never call `chatClient` directly from a
  component. Components dispatch actions (`sendMessage`, `reset`) and read with
  selectors (`useChatStore((s) => s.messages)`).
- **The `/chat` contract types live in `chatClient.ts`** (`ChatMessage`,
  `ChatSource`, `ChatResponse`) and MUST match
  `packages/api/src/routes/chat.ts` exactly. Update both together. Note the
  response has no `threadTitle` / `subject` / `dateRange` fields — those were
  removed.
- **The backend is single-turn:** `sendChat` sends only the last user message,
  not history. Don't quietly switch to multi-turn here without also changing
  the API.
- **Base URL comes from `src/config.ts` (`apiUrl`)** — don't read
  `import.meta.env` or hardcode URLs elsewhere.

## Why

This seam keeps networking testable and the store the single source of truth
for chat state, so UI work (W3) and the typewriter effect (W4) can't smuggle in
ad-hoc network calls or contract drift.
